More broadly, understanding changes in reproductive dynamics will require replacing masting within a wider life-cycle context (CITE). Seed production represents only the first step toward forest regeneration, and climate change may lead into failures in seedling establishment and tree recruitment \citep{Petrie2023}, even in forests where seed production remains synchronous.


